case.name: Loosen Up
case.description: Mercy realizes she's been taking the game too seriously and attempts to loosen up.

case.name: Mercy Is Not A Gamer
case.description: Mercy has misheard a term that D.Va's commenters use, and is now asking what they meant.

case.name: It's A School Day
case.description: Mercy has noticed that an opponent is wearing a school uniform, and it is a school day.

case.name: It's Not A School Day
case.description: Mercy has noticed that an opponent is wearing a school uniform, and it is the weekend or night-time.

case.name: Why So Formal?
case.description: Mercy wonders why her target is wearing such a formal outfit.

case.name: One More Layer
case.description: Mercy notes that she needs prescription eyewear, but wore contacts today rather than glasses.

case.name: Bad Place for a Mask
case.description: Mercy enquires after the reason for a character's mask - and why they would wear it to a strip poker game if they want to keep it on.

case.name: Seeking New Experiences
case.description: Mercy asks if any of the other players have suggestions for interesting activities.

case.name: Casual Sex
case.description: Mercy asks if any of the other players have had "friends with benefits".

case.name: Group Sex
case.description: Mercy asks if any of the other players enjoy the idea of the three-, four-, or more-some.

case.name: Favored Bedroom Role
case.description: Mercy asks if any of the other players have swings of preference between dominance and submission.

case.name: Mercy's Secret Weapon
case.description: When in last place and forced to remove her underwear, Mercy may threaten to make use of her *secret weapon*!

case.name: Mercy's Secret Weapon pt. 2
case.description: Moments after threatening to use her secret weapon, Mercy reveals that there is no secret weapon.

case.name: Companion Invitation
case.description: If there are fewer than four AI players, Mercy asks why a companion character wasn't invited to play on their own.

notes.note: Fun fact: Swiss Miss is not a brand we get in (at least my region of) Australia! Mercy's confusion mirrors my own, before I googled what it was.

Fun fact: Mercy speaks Swiss German, which is more than close enough to German German to know that Mondstadt translates literally to "Moon City". Feel free to have Fischl confused by her association of Mondstadt and the moon, or just brush past it
Is this out of character for Mercy? Yes. I'm playing up her rivalry with Battleborn. If questioned, she will not understand why she feels so compelled to sling insults at Beatrix

Just found the answer to this in Monster Roadtrip - the Human and Monster realms exist seperately, and the Human realm rejects the non-mundane. So when a human dies, they can become a ghost, but once they're a ghost, they'll be pushed out of the Human realm and into the Monster realm instead. That's what happened to Polly
